{"questionId":"35035212","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>At Mirabooka Primary School, a survey found that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>68</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of students have a dog and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>36</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of&nbsp;students have a cat. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>14</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of students have both a dog and a cat.</p>\n<p>This information can be represented in the following Venn diagram, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;represent the percentage of students within each region.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/70d061334915aadefa71688aa34b40032252c269.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Find the probability that a randomly chosen student</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>has a dog given that they do not have a cat.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>54</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>844</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>27</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>84</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>84375</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for a correct denominator (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>64</mn></math> seen), <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for the correct final answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35035212","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.4c.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"has a dog given that they do not have a cat.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}